Pre-Game Insights: Morocco is the clear favorite to win the game, but the Central African Republic will be determined to put up a fight.
Walid Regragui confirmed his players’ readiness for tonight’s game, including the new additions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be broadcast live on Moroccan sports networks, including Arryadia.
The game will kick off this evening at 8:00 pm GMT+1 at the Stade d’Honneur in Oujda.
The Atlas Lions have shown strong form in the ongoing qualifiers, securing key victories over Gabon and Lesotho.
Others: Morocco's national football team will face the Central African Republic today in an African Cup of Nations (AFCON) qualification match, as they aim to solidify their lead in Group B.
Walid Regragui’s squad will enter the match with confidence, having scored 13 goals and conceded only three in their last five matches.
However, the team will be without several key players like Hakim Ziyech, Noussair Mazraoui, and Brahim Diaz due to injuries.
